        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued March 31 at 6:27AM CDT until March 31 at 7:30AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>SVRBMX

The National Weather Service in Birmingham has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Marion County in northwestern Alabama...
Fayette County in west central Alabama...

* Until 730 AM CDT.

* At 627 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 6 miles southeast of Tremont to near Sulligent to
near Steens, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Tucker, Stone Wall, Bankston, Wayside, Richard Arthur Field,
Winfield, Fayette County Public Lake, Fayette, Upper Bear Creek
Reservoir, Brilliant, Guin, Gu-
Win, Bear Creek, Glen Allen, Piney Grove, Bluff, Bazemore, Boley
Springs, Tessner, and Berry.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
